laughter /ˈlɑːftə/

1. N-UNCOUNT Laughter is the sound of people laughing, for example, because they are amused or happy. 笑声 

例： Their laughter filled the corridor. 他们的笑声充满了走廊。 

例： He delivered the line perfectly, and everybody roared with laughter. 他完美地演绎了这句台词，所有的人都哈哈大笑起来。

